#!/bin/bash
# SessionStart hook: remind agent that codebase-memory-mcp tools exist.
# Installed by codebase-memory-mcp; slimmed 2026-07-04 (original in
# ~/.claude/backups/pre-optimize-2026-07-04/).
# Only fires inside a git repo (proxy for "code project") — in docs,
# config, or scratch directories the reminder is pure context tax.
git -C "${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR:-$PWD}" rev-parse --is-inside-work-tree >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 0
cat << 'REMINDER'
Code discovery: prefer codebase-memory-mcp tools for structural code queries —
search_graph (find symbols), trace_path (call chains), get_code_snippet,
get_architecture, search_code (graph-augmented grep). Run index_repository
first if the project isn't indexed. Grep/Glob/Read remain fine for text,
configs, and non-code files; always Read a file before editing it.
REMINDER
